				<p><bibl><ptr target="bib:ThaMyat1963_01"/><citedRange>78</citedRange></bibl> reproduces an eye copy of one face of the inscription, reported to have been sent with a letter dated 29 Oct. 1894 from A. R. Bricks, Officiating Commissioner, Arakan Division, to Dr. D. E. Hultzsch, Government Epigraphist, Madras; no transliteration is provided. <bibl><ptr target="bib:Luce1985_01"/><citedRange>I, 50, 57 n. 22, 150</citedRange></bibl>, summarizes earlier information and sources. <bibl><ptr target="bib:SeinWin2016_01"/><citedRange>189-93</citedRange></bibl> transliterates part of the inscription (in Burmese script). We provide a new provisional reading from the early eye copy and from published estampages and our own photographs.</p>
